    "Simultaneously, E g decreases and reaches a minimum around the first minimum of the droplet oscillation (3).",
    "The surface energy E s decreases during the initial wetting of the substrate, but subsequently increases again as the droplet spreads, reaching a local maximum near the oscillation minimum.",
    "Consequently, E d rises rapidly, reflecting energy dissipation due to viscous effects.",
